title: Desperado
text: A gunslinger is embroiled in a war with a local drug runner.

title: The Crow
text: A man brutally murdered comes back to life as an undead avenger of his and his fiancÃ©e's murder.

title: Falling Down
text: An unemployed defense worker frustrated with the various flaws he sees in society, begins to psychotically and violently lash out against them.

title: Percy Jackson & the Olympians: The Lightning Thief
text: A teenager discovers he's the descendant of a Greek god and sets out on an adventure to settle an on-going battle between the gods.

title: A Knight's Tale
text: After his master dies, a peasant squire, fueled by his desire for food and glory, creates a new identity for himself as a knight.

title: The Woman in Black
text: A young lawyer travels to a remote village where he discovers the vengeful ghost of a scorned woman is terrorizing the locals.

title: Chicken Run
text: Chicken Run is a comedy escape drama with a touch of passion set on a sinister Yorkshire chicken farm in 1950s England.

title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
text: After an encounter with U.F.O.s, a line worker feels undeniably drawn to an isolated area in the wilderness where something spectacular is about to happen.

title: The Perfect Storm
text: An unusually intense storm pattern catches some commercial fishermen unaware and puts them in mortal danger.

title: Hitman
text: A gun-for-hire known only as Agent 47 hired by a group known only as 'The Organization' is ensnared in a political conspiracy, which finds him pursued by both Interpol and the Russian military as he treks across Russia and Eastern Europe.

title: The Life Aquatic with Steve Zissou
text: With a plan to exact revenge on a mythical shark that killed his partner, oceanographer Steve Zissou rallies a crew that includes his estranged wife, a journalist, and a man who may or may not be his son.

title: Michael Clayton
text: A law firm brings in its "fixer" to remedy the situation after a lawyer has a breakdown while representing a chemical company that he knows is guilty in a multi-billion dollar class action suit.

title: Milk
text: The story of Harvey Milk, and his struggles as an American gay activist who fought for gay rights and became California's first openly gay elected official.

title: Letters from Iwo Jima
text: The story of the battle of Iwo Jima between the United States and Imperial Japan during World War II, as told from the perspective of the Japanese who fought it.

title: How the Grinch Stole Christmas
text: A creature is intent on stealing Christmas.

title: The Talented Mr. Ripley
text: In late 1950s New York, Tom Ripley, a young underachiever, is sent to Italy to retrieve a rich and spoiled millionaire playboy, named Dickie Greenleaf. But when the errand fails, Ripley takes extreme measures.

title: The Ghost Writer
text: A ghostwriter hired to complete the memoirs of a former British prime minister uncovers secrets that put his own life in jeopardy.

title: Shoot 'Em Up
text: A man named Mr. Smith delivers a woman's baby during a shootout, and is then called upon to protect the newborn from the army of gunmen.

title: King Arthur
text: A demystified take on the tale of King Arthur and the Knights of the Round Table.

title: The Insider
text: A research chemist comes under personal and professional attack when he decides to appear in a "60 Minutes" expose on Big Tobacco.

title: The Tree of Life
text: The story of a family in Waco, Texas in 1956. The eldest son witnesses the loss of innocence and struggles with his parents' conflicting teachings.

title: Dirty Dancing
text: Spending the summer in a holiday camp with her family, Frances "Baby" Houseman falls in love with the camp's dance instructor Johnny Castle.

title: Who Framed Roger Rabbit
text: A toon hating detective is a cartoon rabbit's only hope to prove his innocence when he is accused of murder.

title: Erin Brockovich
text: An unemployed single mother becomes a legal assistant and almost single-handedly brings down a California power company accused of polluting a city's water supply.

title: Hard Candy
text: A teenage girl raids a man's home, suspecting he is a pedophile, in order to expose him.

title: Rushmore
text: The extracurricular king of Rushmore preparatory school is put on academic probation.

title: The Darjeeling Limited
text: A year after their father's funeral, three brothers travel across India by train in an attempt to bond with each other.

title: Road Trip
text: Four friends take off on an 1800 mile road trip to retrieve an illicit tape mistakenly mailed to a girl friend.

title: Spaceballs
text: Planet Spaceball's President Skroob sends Lord Dark Helmet to steal Planet Druidia's abundant supply of air to replenish their own, and only Lone Starr can stop them.

title: Ice Age: Continental Drift
text: Manny, Diego, and Sid embark upon another adventure after their continent is set adrift. Using an iceberg as a ship, they encounter sea creatures and battle pirates as they explore a new world.

title: The Mask of Zorro
text: A young thief, seeking revenge over the death of his brother, is trained by the once great, but aged Zorro, who is also seeking a vengeance of his own.

title: Gremlins
text: A boy inadvertantly breaks 3 important rules concerning his new pet and unleashes a horde of malevolently mischievous monsters on a small town.

title: Layer Cake
text: A successful cocaine dealer gets two tough assignments from his boss on the eve of his planned early retirement.

title: The Vow
text: A car accident puts Paige in a coma, and when she wakes up with severe memory loss, her husband Leo works to win her heart again.

title: Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back
text: The comic 'Bluntman and Chronic' is based on real-life stoners Jay and Silent Bob, so when they get no profit from a big-screen adaptation they set out to wreck the movie.

title: Madagascar: Escape 2 Africa
text: The animals try to fly back to New York City, but crash-land on an African wildlife refuge, where Alex is reunited with his parents.

title: Wild Wild West
text: The two best hired guns in the West must save President Grant from the clutches of a 19th century inventor-villain.

title: Vantage Point
text: The attempted assassination of the American President is told and re-told from several different perspectives.

title: Misery
text: Paul Sheldon, a successful novelist, is rescued after a snow storm by his "Number One Fan" and must rewrite his latest novel to her liking in order to stay alive.

title: Basic Instinct
text: A police detective is in charge of the investigation of a brutal murder, in which a beautiful and seductive woman could be involved.

title: He's Just Not That Into You
text: The Baltimore-set movie of interconnecting story arcs deals with the challenges of reading or misreading human behavior.

title: Shrek Forever After
text: Rumpelstiltskin tricks a mid-life crisis burdened Shrek into allowing himself to be erased from existence and cast in a dark alternate timeline where Rumpel rules supreme.

title: Resident Evil: Afterlife
text: While still out to destroy the evil Umbrella Corporation, Alice joins a group of survivors living in a prison surrounded by the infected who also want to relocate to the mysterious but supposedly unharmed safe haven known only as Arcadia.

title: Fantastic Mr. Fox
text: An urbane fox cannot resist returning to his farm raiding ways and then must help his community survive the farmers' retaliation.

title: Miss Congeniality
text: An FBI agent must go undercover in the Miss United States beauty pageant to prevent a group from bombing the event.

title: Once Upon a Time in Mexico
text: Hitman "El Mariachi" becomes involved in international espionage involving a psychotic CIA agent and a corrupt Mexican general.

title: The Abyss
text: A civilian diving team are enlisted to search for a lost nuclear submarine and face danger while encountering an alien aquatic species.

title: Adventureland
text: In the summer of 1987, a college graduate takes a 'nowhere' job at his local amusement park, only to find it's the perfect course to get him prepared for the real world.

title: Sinister
text: A true-crime writer finds a cache of 8mm home movies films that suggest the murder he is currently researching is the work of a serial killer whose career dates back to the 1960s.

title: Definitely, Maybe
text: A political consultant tries to explain his impending divorce and past relationships to his 11-year-old daughter.

title: Ghostbusters II
text: The discovery of a massive river of ectoplasm and a resurgence of spectral activity allows the staff of Ghostbusters to revive the business.

title: Orphan
text: A husband and wife who recently lost their baby adopt a 9-year-old girl who is not nearly as innocent as she claims to be.

title: Abraham Lincoln: Vampire Hunter
text: Abraham Lincoln, the 16th President of the United States, discovers vampires are planning to take over the United States. He makes it his mission to eliminate them.

title: A Fistful of Dollars
text: A wandering gunfighter plays two rival families against each other in a town torn apart by greed, pride, and revenge.

title: Shark Tale
text: When a son of a gangster shark boss is accidently killed while on the hunt, his would-be prey and his vegetarian brother both decide to use the incident to their own advantage.

title: The Imaginarium of Doctor Parnassus
text: A traveling theater company gives its audience much more than they were expecting.

title: Lethal Weapon 4
text: With personal crises and age weighing in on them, LAPD officers Riggs and Murtaugh must contend with a deadly Chinese crimelord trying to get his brother out of prison.

title: Lethal Weapon 3
text: Martin Riggs and Roger Murtaugh pursue an arms dealer who is a former LAPD officer.

title: Blade: Trinity
text: Blade, now a wanted man by the FBI, must join forces with the Nightstalkers to face his most challenging enemy yet: Dracula

title: Date Night
text: In New York City, a case of mistaken identity turns a bored married couple's attempt at a glamorous and romantic evening into something more thrilling and dangerous.

title: Man on a Ledge
text: As a police psychologist works to talk down an ex-con who is threatening to jump from a Manhattan hotel rooftop, the biggest diamond heist ever committed is in motion.

title: The Hills Have Eyes
text: A suburban American family is being stalked by a group of psychotic people who live in the desert, far away from civilization.

title: Modern Times
text: The Tramp struggles to live in modern industrial society with the help of a young homeless woman.

title: Primal Fear
text: An altar boy is accused of murdering a priest, and the truth is buried several layers deep.

title: Need for Speed
text: Fresh from prison, a street racer who was framed by a wealthy business associate joins a cross country race with revenge in mind. His ex-partner, learning of the plan, places a massive bounty on his head as the race begins..

title: Blades of Glory
text: In 2002, two rival Olympic ice skaters were stripped of their gold medals and permanently banned from men's single competition. Presently, however, they've found a loophole that will allow them to qualify as a pairs team.

title: Blue Velvet
text: The discovery of a severed human ear found in a field leads a young man on an investigation related to a beautiful, mysterious nightclub singer and a group of psychopathic criminals who have kidnapped her child.

title: Flightplan
text: A bereaved woman and her daughter are flying home from Berlin to America. At 30,000 feet, the child vanishes, and nobody will admit she was ever on the plane.

title: Tarzan
text: A man raised by gorillas must decide where he really belongs when he discovers he is a human.

title: Mr. Brooks
text: A psychological thriller about a man who is sometimes controlled by his murder-and-mayhem-loving alter ego.

title: Cape Fear
text: A convicted rapist, released from prison after serving a fourteen-year sentence, stalks the family of the lawyer who originally defended him.

title: Hercules
genre: [u'Animation', u'Adventure', u'Comedy', u'Family', u'Fantasy', u'Musical', u'Romance']
text: The son of the Greek Gods Zeus and Hera is stripped of his immortality as an infant and must become a true hero in order to reclaim it.

title: Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby
text: #1 NASCAR driver Ricky Bobby stays atop the heap thanks to a pact with his best friend and teammate, Cal Naughton, Jr. But when a French Formula One driver, makes his way up the ladder, Ricky Bobby's talent and devotion are put to the test.

title: Over the Hedge
text: A scheming raccoon fools a mismatched family of forest creatures into helping him repay a debt of food, by invading the new suburban sprawl that popped up while they were hibernating...and learns a lesson about family himself.

title: Analyze This
text: A comedy about a psychiatrist whose number one-patient is an insecure mob boss.

title: Mud
text: Two young boys encounter a fugitive and form a pact to help him evade the vigilantes that are on his trail and to reunite him with his true love.

title: Happy Feet
text: Into the world of the Emperor Penguins, who find their soul mates through song, a penguin is born who cannot sing. But he can tap dance something fierce!

title: Smokin' Aces
text: When a Las Vegas performer-turned-snitch named Buddy Israel decides to turn state's evidence and testify against the mob, it seems that a whole lot of people would like to make sure he's no longer breathing.

title: From Hell
text: In Victorian Era London, a troubled clairvoyant police detective investigates the murders by Jack The Ripper.

title: Mama
text: Annabel and Lucas are faced with the challenge of raising his young nieces that were left alone in the forest for 5 years.... but how alone were they?

title: The Longest Yard
text: Prison inmates form a football team to challenge the prison guards.

title: The Lovely Bones
text: Centers on a young girl who has been murdered and watches over her family - and her killer - from purgatory. She must weigh her desire for vengeance against her desire for her family to heal.

title: Lethal Weapon 2
text: Riggs and Murtaugh are on the trail of South African diplomats who are using their immunity to engage in criminal activities.

title: Army of Darkness
text: A man is accidentally transported to 1300 A.D., where he must battle an army of the dead and retrieve the Necronomicon so he can return home.

title: Next
text: A Las Vegas magician who can see into the future is pursued by FBI agents seeking to use his abilities to prevent a nuclear terrorist attack.

title: The Heat
text: An uptight FBI Special Agent is paired with a foul-mouthed Boston cop to take down a ruthless drug lord.

title: Mr. Nobody
text: A boy stands on a station platform as a train is about to leave. Should he go with his mother or stay with his father? Infinite possibilities arise from this decision. As long as he doesn't choose, anything is possible.

title: I Am Sam
text: A mentally handicapped man fights for custody of his 7-year-old daughter, and in the process teaches his cold hearted lawyer the value of love and family.

title: Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs
text: Snow White, pursued by a jealous queen, hides with the Dwarfs; the queen feeds her a poison apple, but the handsome prince awakens her with a kiss.

title: Starsky & Hutch
text: Two streetwise cops bust criminals in their red-and-white Ford Torino with the help of police snitch called Huggy Bear.

title: The Sorcerer's Apprentice
text: Master sorcerer Balthazar Blake must find and train Merlin's descendant to defeat dark sorceress Morgana le Fey.

title: Rounders
text: A young man is a reformed gambler who must return to playing big stakes poker to help a friend pay off loan sharks.

title: Melancholia
text: Two sisters find their already strained relationship challenged as a mysterious new planet threatens to collide with Earth.

title: The Iron Giant
genre: [u'Animation', u'Action', u'Adventure', u'Comedy', u'Drama', u'Family', u'Sci-Fi']
text: A boy makes friends with an innocent alien giant robot that a paranoid government agent wants to destroy.

title: Antz
text: A rather neurotic ant tries to break from his totalitarian society while trying to win the affection of the princess he loves.

title: Galaxy Quest
text: The alumni cast of a space opera television series have to play their roles as the real thing when an alien race needs their help.

title: Superman
text: An alien orphan is sent from his dying planet to Earth, where he grows up to become his adoptive home's first and greatest superhero.

title: Spy Game
text: Retiring CIA agent Nathan Muir recalls his training of Tom Bishop while working against agency politics to free him from his Chinese captors.

title: Scream 2
text: Two years after the first series of murders, a new psychopath dons the Ghostface costume and a new string of killings begins.

title: Memoirs of a Geisha
text: Nitta Sayuri reveals how she transcended her fishing-village roots and became one of Japan's most celebrated geisha.

title: Invictus
text: Nelson Mandela, in his first term as the South African President, initiates a unique venture to unite the apartheid-torn land: enlist the national rugby team on a mission to win the 1995 Rugby World Cup.

title: Girl, Interrupted
text: Based on writer Susanna Kaysen's account of her 18-month stay at a mental hospital in the 1960s.

title: Beverly Hills Cop
text: A freewheeling Detroit cop pursuing a murder investigation finds himself dealing with the very different culture of Beverly Hills.

title: The Punisher
text: An undercover FBI agent becomes a vigilante assassin and sets out to unleash vengeance upon the corrupt businessman who slew his family.

title: Legally Blonde
text: When a blonde sorority queen is dumped by her boyfriend, she decides to follow him to law school to get him back and, once there, learns she has more legal savvy than she ever imagined.

title: The Man in the Iron Mask
text: The cruel King Louis XIV of France has a secret twin brother who he keeps imprisoned. Can the twin be substituted for the real king?

title: Sleepless in Seattle
text: A recently widowed man's son calls a radio talk-show in an attempt to find his father a partner.

title: S.W.A.T.
text: An imprisoned drug kingpin offers a huge cash reward to anyone that can break him out of police custody and only the LAPD's Special Weapons and Tactics team can prevent it.

title: Cold Mountain
text: In the waning days of the American Civil War, a wounded soldier embarks on a perilous journey back home to Cold Mountain, North Carolina to reunite with his sweetheart.

title: Tucker and Dale vs. Evil
text: Tucker & Dale are on vacation at their dilapidated mountain cabin when they are attacked by a group of preppy college kids.

title: The Purge
text: In the future, a wealthy family is held hostage for harboring the target of a murderous syndicate during the Purge, a 12-hour period in which any and all crime is legalized.

title: The Cable Guy
text: A lonely and disturbed cable guy raised on television just wants a new friend, but his target, a designer, rejects him, with bad consequences.

title: Pandorum
text: A pair of crew members aboard a spaceship wake up with no knowledge of their mission or their identities.

title: Demolition Man
text: A police officer is brought out of suspended animation in prison to pursue an old ultra-violent nemesis who is loose in a non-violent future society.

title: The Orphanage
text: A woman brings her family back to her childhood home, which used to be an orphanage for handicapped children. Before long, her son starts to communicate with an invisible new friend.

title: Snakes on a Plane
text: An FBI agent takes on a plane full of deadly and poisonous snakes, deliberately released to kill a witness being flown from Honolulu to Los Angeles to testify against a mob boss.

title: Wall Street
text: A young and impatient stockbroker is willing to do anything to get to the top, including trading on illegal inside information taken through a ruthless and greedy corporate raider who takes the youth under his wing.

title: The Boy in the Striped Pajamas
text: Set during World War II, a story seen through the innocent eyes of Bruno, the eight-year-old son of the commandant at a concentration camp, whose forbidden friendship with a Jewish boy on the other side of the camp fence has startling and unexpected consequences.

title: Night at the Museum: Battle of the Smithsonian
text: Security guard Larry Daley infiltrates the Smithsonian Institution in order to rescue Jedediah and Octavius, who have been shipped to the museum by mistake.

title: Evil Dead
text: Five friends head to a remote cabin, where the discovery of a Book of the Dead leads them to unwittingly summon up demons living in the nearby woods. The evil presence possesses them until only one is left to fight for survival.

title: I Now Pronounce You Chuck & Larry
text: Two straight, single Brooklyn firefighters pretend to be a gay couple in order to receive domestic partner benefits.

title: Rocky IV
text: After iron man Drago, a highly intimidating 6-foot-5, 261-pound Soviet athlete, kills Apollo Creed in an exhibition match, Rocky comes to the heart of Russia for 15 pile-driving boxing rounds of revenge.

title: Final Destination 2
text: When Kimberly has a violent premonition of a highway pileup she blocks the freeway, keeping a few others meant to die, safe...Or are they? The survivors mysteriously start dying and it's up to Kimberly to stop it before she's next.

title: Brüno
text: Flamboyant Austrian fashionista BrÃ¼no takes his show to America.

title: Riddick
text: Left for dead on a sun-scorched planet, Riddick finds himself up against an alien race of predators. Activating an emergency beacon alerts two ships: one carrying a new breed of mercenary, the other captained by a man from Riddick's past.

title: Transporter 3
text: Frank Martin puts the driving gloves on to deliver Valentina, the kidnapped daughter of a Ukranian government official, from Marseilles to Odessa on the Black Sea. En route, he has to contend with thugs who want to intercept Valentina's safe delivery and not let his personal feelings get in the way of his dangerous objective.

title: The Karate Kid
text: A handyman/martial arts master agrees to teach a bullied boy karate and shows him that there is more to the martial art than fighting.

title: Clerks II
text: A calamity at Dante and Randall's shops sends them looking for new horizons - but they ultimately settle at Mooby's, a fictional Disney-McDonald's-style fast-food empire.

title: Kingsman: The Secret Service
text: A spy organization recruits an unrefined, but promising street kid into the agency's ultra-competitive training program, just as a global threat emerges from a twisted tech genius.

title: Anchorman 2: The Legend Continues
text: With the 70s behind him, San Diego's top rated newsman, Ron Burgundy, returns to take New York's first 24-hour news channel by storm.

title: The Last Airbender
text: Follows the adventures of Aang, a young successor to a long line of Avatars, who must master all four elements and stop the Fire Nation from enslaving the Water Tribes and the Earth Kingdom.

title: Dude, Where's My Car?
text: Two potheads wake up after a night of partying and cannot remember where they parked their car.

title: The Emperor's New Groove
text: Emperor Kuzco is turned into a llama by his ex-administrator Yzma, and must now regain his throne with the help of Pacha, the gentle llama herder.

title: 16 Blocks
text: An aging alcoholic cop is assigned the task of escorting a witness from police custody to a courthouse 16 blocks away. There are, however, chaotic forces at work that prevent them from making it in one piece.

title: Rush Hour 3
text: After an attempted assassination on Ambassador Han, Lee and Carter head to Paris to protect a French woman with knowledge of the Triads' secret leaders.

title: Scary Movie 2
text: Four teens are tricked by their professor into visiting a haunted house for a school project.

title: Lars and the Real Girl
text: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet.

title: 27 Dresses
text: After serving as a bridesmaid 27 times, a young woman wrestles with the idea of standing by her sister's side as her sibling marries the man she's secretly in love with.

title: State of Play
text: When a congressional aide is killed, a Washington D.C. journalist starts investigating the case involving the congressman, his old college friend.

title: The Bone Collector
text: A quadriplegic ex-homicide detective and his female partner try to track down a serial killer who is terrorizing New York City.

title: The Waterboy
text: A waterboy for a college football team discovers he has a unique tackling ability and becomes a member of the team.

title: Evan Almighty
text: God contacts Congressman Evan Baxter and tells him to build an ark in preparation for a great flood.

title: Harold & Kumar Escape from Guantanamo Bay
text: Follows the cross-country adventures of the pot-smoking duo as they try to outrun authorities who suspect them of being terrorists when they try to sneak a bong on board their flight to Amsterdam.

title: Defiance
text: Jewish brothers in Nazi-occupied Eastern Europe escape into the Belarussian forests, where they join Russian resistance fighters and endeavor to build a village in order to protect themselves and about 1,000 Jewish non-combatants.

title: Green Street Hooligans
text: A wrongfully expelled Harvard undergrad moves to London, where he is introduced to the violent underworld of football hooliganism.

title: RED 2
text: Retired C.I.A. agent Frank Moses reunites his unlikely team of elite operatives for a global quest to track down a missing portable nuclear device.

title: Rise of the Guardians
text: When the evil spirit Pitch launches an assault on Earth, the Immortal Guardians team up to protect the innocence of children all around the world.

title: Buried
text: Paul is a U.S. truck driver working in Iraq. After an attack by a group of Iraqis he wakes to find he is buried alive inside a coffin. With only a lighter and a cell phone it's a race against time to escape this claustrophobic death trap.

title: The Mechanic
text: Follows an elite hit man as he teaches his trade to an apprentice who has a connection to one of his previous victims.

title: Chasing Amy
text: Holden and Banky are comic book artists. Everything's going good for them until they meet Alyssa, also a comic book artist. Holden falls for her, but his hopes are crushed when he finds out she's gay.

title: A Million Ways to Die in the West
text: As a cowardly farmer begins to fall for the mysterious new woman in town, he must put his new-found courage to the test when her husband, a notorious gun-slinger, announces his arrival.

title: Underworld: Rise of the Lycans
text: An origins story centered on the centuries-old feud between the race of aristocratic vampires and their onetime slaves, the Lycans.

title: Coming to America
text: An African prince goes to Queens, New York City to find a wife whom he can respect for her intelligence and will.

title: The Karate Kid
text: Work causes a single mother to move to China with her young son; in his new home, the boy embraces kung fu, taught to him by a master.

title: The Lake House
text: A lonely doctor who once occupied an unusual lakeside home begins exchanging love letters with its former resident, a frustrated architect. They must try to unravel the mystery behind their extraordinary romance before it's too late.

title: The Virgin Suicides
text: A group of male friends become obsessed with five mysterious sisters who are sheltered by their strict, religious parents.

title: Æon Flux
text: Aeon Flux is a mysterious assassin working for the Monicans, a group of rebels trying to overthrow the government. When she is a sent on a mission to kill the Chairman, a whole new mystery is found.

title: JFK
text: A New Orleans DA discovers there's more to the Kennedy assassination than the official story.

title: Good Bye Lenin!
text: In 1990, to protect his fragile mother from a fatal shock after a long coma, a young man must keep her from learning that her beloved nation of East Germany as she knew it has disappeared.

title: The Recruit
text: A brilliant young CIA trainee is asked by his mentor to help find a mole in the Agency.

title: The Polar Express
text: A young boy embarks on a magical adventure to the North Pole on the Polar Express. During his adventure he learns about friendship, bravery, and the spirit of Christmas.

title: Marley & Me
text: A family learns important life lessons from their adorable, but naughty and neurotic dog.

title: Event Horizon
text: A rescue crew investigates a spaceship that disappeared into a black hole and has now returned...with someone or something new on-board.

title: Dazed and Confused
text: The adventures of incoming high school and junior high students on the last day of school, in May of 1976.

title: Johnny English
text: After a sudden attack on the MI5, Johnny English, Britain's most confident yet unintelligent spy, becomes Britain's only spy.

title: The Last Stand
text: The leader of a drug cartel busts out of a courthouse and speeds to the Mexican border, where the only thing in his path is a sheriff and his inexperienced staff.

title: Conan the Barbarian
text: A vengeful barbarian warrior sets off to avenge his tribe and his parents whom were slain by an evil sorcerer and his warriors when he was a boy.

title: War Horse
text: Young Albert enlists to serve in World War I after his beloved horse is sold to the cavalry. Albert's hopeful journey takes him out of England and to the front lines as the war rages on.

title: Gamer
text: In a future mind-controlling game, death row convicts are forced to battle in a 'Doom'-type environment. Convict Kable, controlled by Simon, a skilled teenage gamer, must survive thirty sessions in order to be set free. Or won't he?

title: An Education
text: A coming-of-age story about a teenage girl in 1960s suburban London, and how her life changes with the arrival of a playboy nearly twice her age.

title: Underworld: Awakening
text: When human forces discover the existence of the Vampire and Lycan clans, a war to eradicate both species commences. The vampire warrior Selene leads the battle against humankind.

title: The Secret in Their Eyes
text: A retired legal counselor writes a novel hoping to find closure for one of his past unresolved homicide cases and for his unreciprocated love with his superior - both of which still haunt him decades later.

title: The Fly
text: A brilliant but eccentric scientist begins to transform into a giant man/fly hybrid after one of his experiments goes horribly wrong.

title: The Mummy: Tomb of the Dragon Emperor
text: In the Far East, Alex O'Connell, the son of famed mummy fighters Rick and Evy O'Connell, unearths the mummy of the first Emperor of Qin -- a shape-shifting entity cursed by a witch centuries ago.

title: Dr. No
text: A suave and skilled government agent named James Bond, looks for answers about a missing colleague and the disruption of the American space program.

title: Payback
text: Porter is shot by his wife and best friend and is left to die. When he survives he plots revenge.

title: Dracula Untold
text: As his kingdom is being threatened by the Turks, young prince Vlad Tepes must become a monster feared by his own people in order to obtain the power needed to protect his own family, and the families of his kingdom.

title: Young Frankenstein
text: Dr. Frankenstein's grandson, after years of living down the family reputation, inherits granddad's castle and repeats the experiments.

title: 13 Going on 30
text: A 13 year old girl plays a game on her 13th birthday and wakes up the next day as a 30 year old woman.

title: Rambo: First Blood Part II
text: John Rambo is released from prison by the government for a top-secret covert mission to the last place on Earth he'd want to return - the jungles of Vietnam.

title: The Time Traveler's Wife
text: A romantic drama about a Chicago librarian with a gene that causes him to involuntarily time travel, and the complications it creates for his marriage.

title: The Jungle Book
text: Bagheera the Panther and Baloo the Bear have a difficult time trying to convince a boy to leave the jungle for human civilization.

title: The Kids Are All Right
text: Two children conceived by artificial insemination bring their father into their family life.

title: Clueless
text: A rich high school student tries to boost a new pupil's popularity, but reckons without affairs of the heart getting in the way.

title: Winter's Bone
text: An unflinching Ozark Mountain girl hacks through dangerous social terrain as she hunts down her drug-dealing father while trying to keep her family intact.

title: The Grudge
text: An American nurse living and working in Tokyo is exposed to a mysterious supernatural curse, one that locks a person in a powerful rage before claiming their life and spreading to another victim.

title: Wayne's World
text: Two slacker friends try to promote their public-access cable show.

title: The Constant Gardener
text: A widower is determined to get to the bottom of a potentially explosive secret involving his wife's murder, big business, and corporate corruption.

title: The Men Who Stare at Goats
text: A reporter in Iraq might just have the story of a lifetime when he meets Lyn Cassady, a guy who claims to be a former member of the U.S. Army's New Earth Army, a unit that employs paranormal powers in their missions.

title: Puss in Boots
text: The events leading up to the sword fighting cat's meeting with Shrek and his friends.

title: Remember Me
text: A romantic drama centered on two new lovers: Tyler, whose parents have split in the wake of his brother's suicide, and Ally, who lives each day to the fullest since witnessing her mother's murder.

title: Fun with Dick and Jane
text: An update of the 1977 comedy, Dick and Jane are living the good life. That is until Dick (Jim Carrey) loses his job shortly after getting a promotion that convinced his wife Jane (TÃ©a Leoni) to quit her job. The money is gone, and the house ends up in foreclosure. Dick decides to turn to a hilarious life of crime to pay the bills with his lovely wife by his side. Then together they decide it's time to steal back what Former CEO Jack McCallister (Alec Baldwin) had stolen from them.

title: About Schmidt
text: A man upon retirement embarks on a journey to his estranged daughter's wedding only to discover more about himself and life than he ever expected.

title: Green Zone
text: Discovering covert and faulty intelligence causes a U.S. Army officer to go rogue as he hunts for Weapons of Mass Destruction in an unstable region.

title: 47 Ronin
text: A band of samurai set out to avenge the death and dishonor of their master at the hands of a ruthless shogun.

title: The Last of the Mohicans
text: Three trappers protect a British Colonel's daughters in the midst of the French and Indian War.

title: A Fish Called Wanda
text: In London, four very different people team up to commit armed robbery, then try to doublecross each other for the loot.

title: Tower Heist
text: When a group of hard working guys find out they've fallen victim to a wealthy business man's Ponzi scheme, they conspire to rob his high-rise residence.

title: Shallow Hal
text: A shallow man falls in love with a 300 pound woman because of her "inner beauty".

title: Syriana
text: A politically-charged epic about the state of the oil industry in the hands of those personally involved and affected by it.

title: The Way Way Back
text: Shy 14-year-old Duncan goes on summer vacation with his mother, her overbearing boyfriend, and her boyfriend's daughter. Having a rough time fitting in, Duncan finds an unexpected friend in Owen, manager of the Water Wizz water park.

title: Max Payne
text: Coming together to solve a series of murders in New York City are a police detective whose family was slain as part of a conspiracy and an assassin out to avenge her sister's death. The duo will be hunted by the police, the mob, and a ruthless corporation.

title: Scary Movie 3
text: In the third installment of the Scary Movie franchise, Cindy has to investigate mysterious crop circles and video tapes, and help the President in preventing an alien invasion.

title: 10,000 BC
text: A prehistoric epic that follows a young mammoth hunter's journey through uncharted territory to secure the future of his tribe.

title: Killing Them Softly
text: Jackie Cogan is an enforcer hired to restore order after three dumb guys rob a Mob protected card game, causing the local criminal economy to collapse.

title: Madagascar 3: Europe's Most Wanted
text: Alex, Marty, Gloria and Melman are still fighting to get home to their beloved Big Apple. Their journey takes them through Europe where they find the perfect cover: a traveling circus, which they reinvent - Madagascar style.

title: The Running Man
text: A wrongly convicted man must try to survive a public execution gauntlet staged as a game show.

title: The Naked Gun: From the Files of Police Squad!
text: Incompetent cop Frank Drebin has to foil an attempt to assassinate Queen Elizabeth II.

genre: [u'Animation', u'Action', u'Adventure', u'Drama', u'Fantasy', u'Mystery', u'Sci-Fi', u'Thriller']
text: A rag doll that awakens in a postapocalyptic future holds the key to humanity's salvation.

title: Eragon
text: In his homeland of Alagaesia, a farm boy happens upon a dragon's egg -- a discovery that leads him on a predestined journey where he realized he's the one person who can defend his home against an evil king.

title: Bad Santa
text: A miserable conman and his partner pose as Santa and his Little Helper to rob department stores on Christmas Eve. But they run into problems when the conman befriends a troubled kid, and the security boss discovers the plot.

title: We Bought a Zoo
text: Set in Southern California, a father moves his young family to the countryside to renovate and re-open a struggling zoo.

title: The Wedding Singer
text: Robbie, the singer and Julia, the waitress are both engaged to be married but to the wrong people. Fortune intervenes to help them discover each other.

title: Monsters vs. Aliens
text: A woman transformed into a giant after she is struck by a meteorite on her wedding day becomes part of a team of monsters sent in by the U.S. government to defeat an alien mastermind trying to take over Earth.

title: Mad Max 2: The Road Warrior
text: In the post-apocalyptic Australian wasteland, a cynical drifter agrees to help a small, gasoline rich, community escape a band of bandits.

title: Along Came Polly
text: A buttoned up newlywed finds his too organized life falling into chaos when he falls in love with an old classmate.

title: Reign of Fire
text: A brood of fire-breathing dragons emerges from the earth and begins setting fire to everything, establishing dominance over the planet.

title: The Negotiator
text: In a desperate attempt to prove his innocence, a skilled police negotiator accused of corruption and murder takes hostages in a government office to gain the time he needs to find the truth.

title: Legends of the Fall
text: Epic tale of three brothers and their father living in the remote wilderness of 1900s USA and how their lives are affected by nature, history, war, and love.

title: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre
text: After picking up a traumatized young hitchhiker, five friends find themselves stalked and hunted by a deformed chainsaw-wielding killer and his family of equally psychopathic killers.

title: Mr. Deeds
text: A sweet-natured, small-town guy inherits a controlling stake in a media conglomerate and begins to do business his way.

title: The Third Man
text: Pulp novelist Holly Martins travels to shadowy, postwar Vienna, only to find himself investigating the mysterious death of an old friend, black-market opportunist Harry Lime.

title: Saw IV
text: Jigsaw and his apprentice Amanda are dead. Now, upon the news of Detective Kerry's murder, two seasoned FBI profilers...

title: Evil Dead II
text: The lone survivor of an onslaught of flesh-possessing spirits holds up in a cabin with a group of strangers while the demons continue their attack.

title: She's the Man
text: When her brother decides to ditch for a couple weeks in London, Viola heads over to his elite boarding school, disguises herself as him, and proceeds to fall for one of her soccer teammates. Little does she realize she's not the only one with romantic troubles, as she, as he, gets in the middle of a series of intermingled love affairs.

title: 8MM
text: A private investigator is hired to discover if a "snuff film" is authentic or not.

title: Four Weddings and a Funeral
text: Over the course of five social occasions, a committed bachelor must consider the notion that he may have discovered love.

title: The Campaign
text: An incumbent congressman embroiled in personal scandal faces a no-holds-barred challenge from a naive newcomer funded by two unscrupulous billionaire lobbyist brothers.

title: Accepted
text: A high school slacker who's rejected by every school he applies to opts to create his own institution of higher learning, the South Harmon Institute of Technology, on a rundown piece of property near his hometown.

title: Four Brothers
text: Four brothers look to avenge their mother's death.

title: Ray
text: The story of the life and career of the legendary rhythm and blues musician Ray Charles, from his humble beginnings in the South, where he went blind at age seven, to his meteoric rise to stardom during the 1950s and 1960s.

title: Dogville
text: A woman on the run from the mob is reluctantly accepted in a small Colorado town. In exchange, she agrees to work for them. As a search visits town, she finds out that their support has a price. Yet her dangerous secret is never far away...

title: Daybreakers
text: In the year 2019, a plague has transformed almost every human into vampires. Faced with a dwindling blood supply, the fractured dominant race plots their survival; meanwhile, a researcher works with a covert band of vamps on a way to save humankind.

title: Bridge to Terabithia
text: A preteen's life turns upside down when he befriends the new girl in school and they imagine a whole new fantasy world to escape reality.

title: Matchstick Men
text: A phobic con artist and his protÃ©gÃ© are on the verge of pulling off a lucrative swindle when the former's teenage daughter arrives unexpectedly.

title: Saving Mr. Banks
text: Author

title: The Time Machine
text: Hoping to alter the events of the past, a 19th century inventor instead travels 800,000 years into the future, where he finds humankind divided into two warring races.

title: Punch-Drunk Love
text: A psychologically troubled novelty supplier is nudged towards a romance with an English woman, all the while being extorted by a phone-sex line run by a crooked mattress salesman, and purchasing stunning amounts of pudding.

title: Rocky III
text: Rocky has been holding the title as the heavyweight champion until he is defeated by a brutal challenger, and now must regain his fighting spirit through a big rematch, trained by an unlikely ally: his old nemesis Apollo Creed.

title: Crank: High Voltage
text: Chelios faces a Chinese mobster who has stolen his nearly indestructible heart and replaced it with a battery-powered ticker that requires regular jolts of electricity to keep working.

title: Chef
text: A chef who loses his restaurant job starts up a food truck in an effort to reclaim his creative promise, while piecing back together his estranged family.

title: Pocahontas
genre: [u'Animation', u'Adventure', u'Drama', u'Family', u'History', u'Musical', u'Romance']
text: An English soldier and the daughter of an Algonquin chief share a romance when English colonists invade seventeenth-century Virginia.

title: Never Let Me Go
text: A love triangle develops between three friends who came of age at a mysterious, secluded boarding school and are destined to lead brief lives.

title: Killer Elite
text: When his mentor is taken captive by a disgraced Arab sheik, a killer-for-hire is forced into action. His mission: kill three members of Britain's elite Special Air Service responsible for the death of his sons.

title: This Is Spinal Tap
text: Spinal Tap, one of England's loudest bands, is chronicled by film director Marty DeBergi on what proves to be a fateful tour.

title: Horton Hears a Who!
text: Horton the Elephant struggles to protect a microscopic community from his neighbors who refuse to believe it exists.

title: Furious Seven
text: Deckard Shaw seeks revenge against Dominic Toretto and his family for his comatose brother.

title: The 13th Warrior
text: A man, having fallen in love with the wrong woman, is sent by the sultan himself on a diplomatic mission to a distant land as an ambassador. Stopping at a Viking village port to restock on supplies, he finds himself unwittingly embroiled on a quest to banish a mysterious threat in a distant Viking land.

title: Hall Pass
text: Rick and Fred, two husbands who are having difficulty in their marriages, are given a Hall Pass by their wives: for one week, they can do whatever they want.

title: Kindergarten Cop
text: A tough cop is given his most difficult assignment ever: to masquerade as a kindergarten teacher in order to find a drug dealer.

title: The Kingdom
text: A team of U.S. government agents is sent to investigate the bombing of an American facility in the Middle East.

title: The Count of Monte Cristo
text: A young man, falsely imprisoned by his jealous "friends," escapes and uses a hidden treasure to exact his revenge

title: Savages
text: Pot growers Ben and Chon face off against the Mexican drug cartel who kidnapped their shared girlfriend.

title: Spring Breakers
text: Four college girls hold up a restaurant in order to fund their spring break vacation. While partying/drinking/taking drugs they are arrested only to be bailed out by a drug and arms dealer.

title: Glory
text: Robert Gould Shaw leads the US Civil War's first all-black volunteer company, fighting prejudices of both his own Union army and the Confederates.

title: Lilo & Stitch
genre: [u'Animation', u'Adventure', u'Comedy', u'Drama', u'Family', u'Fantasy', u'Music', u'Sci-Fi']
text: A Hawaiian girl adopts an unusual pet who is actually a notorious extra-terrestrial fugitive from the law.

title: Pleasantville
text: Two 1990s teenagers find themselves in a 1950s sitcom where their influence begins to profoundly change that complacent world.

title: Metropolis
text: In a futuristic city sharply divided between the working class and the city planners, the son of the city's mastermind falls in love with a working class prophet who predicts the coming of a savior to mediate their differences.

title: Funny People
text: When seasoned comedian George Simmons learns of his terminal, inoperable health condition, his desire to form a genuine friendship cause him to take a relatively green performer under his wing as his opening act.

title: Australia
text: Set in northern Australia before World War II, an English aristocrat who inherits a sprawling ranch reluctantly pacts with a stock-man in order to protect her new property from a takeover plot. As the pair drive 2,000 head of cattle over unforgiving landscape, they experience the bombing of Darwin, Australia, by Japanese forces firsthand.

title: I Know What You Did Last Summer
text: Four teens are in great danger one year after their car hits a stranger whose body they dump in the sea.

title: Last Action Hero
text: With the help of a magic ticket, a young film fan is transported into the fictional world of his favorite action film character.

title: Miller's Crossing
text: Tom Regan, an advisor to a Prohibition-era crime boss, tries to keep the peace between warring mobs but gets caught in divided loyalties.

title: Monster
text: Based on the life of Aileen Wuornos, a Daytona Beach prostitute who became a serial killer.

title: The Score
text: An aging thief hopes to retire and live off his ill-gotten wealth when a young kid convinces him into doing one last heist.

title: Idiocracy
text: Private Joe Bauers, the definition of "average American", is selected by the Pentagon to be the guinea pig for a top-secret hibernation program. Forgotten, he awakes five centuries in the future. He discovers a society so incredibly dumbed down that he's easily the most intelligent person alive.

title: Hollow Man
text: Scientists discover how to make people invisible, but their test subject becomes an insane killer who stalks them.

title: Flags of Our Fathers
text: The life stories of the six men who raised the flag at The Battle of Iwo Jima, a turning point in WWII.

title: Contraband
text: To protect his brother-in-law from a drug lord, a former smuggler heads to Panama to score millions of dollars in counterfeit bills.

title: The Expendables 3
text: Barney augments his team with new blood for a personal battle: to take down Conrad Stonebanks, the Expendables co-founder and notorious arms trader who is hell bent on wiping out Barney and every single one of his associates.

title: Jack the Giant Slayer
text: The ancient war between humans and a race of giants is reignited when Jack, a young farmhand fighting for a kingdom and the love of a princess, opens a gateway between the two worlds.

title: Man on the Moon
text: The life and career of a legendary comedian, Andy Kaufman.

title: Evolution
text: A firefighting cadet, two college professors, and a geeky-but-sexy government scientist work against an alien organism that has been rapidly evolving ever since its arrival on Earth inside a meteor.

title: Devil
text: A group of people are trapped in an elevator and the Devil is mysteriously amongst them.

title: She's Out of My League
text: An average Joe meets the perfect woman, but his lack of confidence and the influence of his friends and family begin to pick away at the relationship.

title: Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle
text: The Angels investigate a series of murders which occur after the theft of a witness protection profile database.

title: Manhattan
text: The life of a divorced television writer dating a teenage girl is further complicated when he falls in love with his best friend's mistress.

title: Christmas Vacation
text: The Griswold family's plans for a big family Christmas predictably turn into a big disaster.

title: 101 Dalmatians
text: When a litter of dalmatian puppies are abducted by the minions of Cruella De Vil, the parents must find them before she uses them for a diabolical fashion statement.

title: The Hours
text: The story of how the novel "Mrs. Dalloway" affects three generations of women, all of whom, in one way or another, have had to deal with suicide in their lives.

title: This Is 40
text: Pete and Debbie are both about to turn 40, their kids hate each other, both of their businesses are failing, they're on the verge of losing their house, and their relationship is threatening to fall apart.

title: The Watch
text: Four men who form a neighborhood watch group as a way to get out of their day-to-day family routines find themselves defending the Earth from an alien invasion.

title: It's Kind of a Funny Story
text: A clinically depressed teenager gets a new start after he checks himself into an adult psychiatric ward.

title: Billy Madison
text: In order to inherit his fed up father's hotel empire, an immature and lazy man must repeat grades 1-12 all over again.

title: Scream 4
text: Ten years have passed, and Sidney Prescott, who has put herself back together thanks in part to her writing, is visited by the Ghostface Killer.

title: Resident Evil: Retribution
text: Alice fights alongside a resistance movement to regain her freedom from an Umbrella Corporation testing facility.

title: Bee Movie
text: Barry B. Benson, a bee just graduated from college, is disillusioned at his lone career choice: making honey. On a special trip outside the hive, Barry's life is saved by Vanessa, a florist in New York City. As their relationship blossoms, he discovers humans actually eat honey, and subsequently decides to sue them.

title: Wild Hogs
text: A group of suburban biker wannabes looking for adventure hit the open road, but get more than they bargained for when they encounter a New Mexico gang called the Del Fuegos.

title: Space Jam
genre: [u'Animation', u'Adventure', u'Comedy', u'Family', u'Fantasy', u'Sci-Fi', u'Sport']
text: Michael Jordan agrees to help the Looney Toons play a basketball game vs. alien slavers to determine their freedom.

title: The 6th Day
text: Futuristic action about a man who meets a clone of himself and stumbles into a grand conspiracy about clones taking over the world.

title: Carrie
text: A reimagining of the classic horror tale about Carrie White, a shy girl outcast by her peers and sheltered by her deeply religious mother, who unleashes telekinetic terror on her small town after being pushed too far at her senior prom.

title: Last Vegas
text: Three sixty-something friends take a break from their day-to-day lives to throw a bachelor party in Las Vegas for their last remaining single pal.

title: Point Break
text: An FBI agent goes undercover to catch a gang of bank robbers who may be surfers.

title: The Break-Up
text: In a bid to keep their luxurious condo from their significant other, a couple's break-up proceeds to get uglier and nastier by the moment.

title: One Hour Photo
text: An employee of a one-hour photo lab becomes obsessed with a young suburban family.

title: Sex and the City
text: A New York writer on sex and love is finally getting married to her Mr. Big. But her three best girlfriends must console her after one of them inadvertently leads Mr. Big to jilt her.

title: Mary Poppins
text: A magic nanny comes to work for a cold banker's unhappy family.

title: J. Edgar
text: J. Edgar Hoover, powerful head of the F.B.I. for nearly 50 years, looks back on his professional and personal life.

title: This Is England
text: A story about a troubled boy growing up in England, set in 1983. He comes across a few skinheads on his way home from school, after a fight. They become his new best friends even like family. Based on experiences of director Shane Meadows.

title: Any Given Sunday
text: A behind-the-scenes look at the life-and-death struggles of modern-day gladiators and those who lead them.

title: Mallrats
text: Both dumped by their girlfriends, two best friends seek refuge in the local mall.

title: What Lies Beneath
text: The wife of a university research scientist believes that her lakeside Vermont home is haunted by a ghost - or that she is losing her mind.

title: The Mortal Instruments: City of Bones
text: When her mother disappears, Clary Fray learns that she descends from a line of warriors who protect our world from demons. She joins forces with others like her and heads into a dangerous alternate New York called Downworld.

title: Doubt
text: A Catholic school principal questions a priest's ambiguous relationship with a troubled young student.

title: Honey, I Shrunk the Kids
text: The scientist father of a teenage girl and boy accidentally shrinks his and two other neighborhood teens to the size of insects. Now the teens must fight diminutive dangers as the father searches for them.

title: In the Name of the Father
text: A man's coerced confession to an IRA bombing he did not commit results in the imprisonment of his father as well. An English lawyer fights to free them.

title: Lara Croft Tomb Raider: The Cradle of Life
text: Adventuress Lara Croft goes on a quest to save the mythical Pandora's Box before an evil scientist and recruits a former Marine turned mercenary to assist her.

title: The Judge
text: Big city lawyer Hank Palmer returns to his childhood home where his father, the town's judge, is suspected of murder. Hank sets out to discover the truth and, along the way, reconnects with his estranged family.

title: The Chronicles of Narnia: The Voyage of the Dawn Treader
text: Lucy and Edmund Pevensie return to Narnia with their cousin Eustace where they meet up with Prince Caspian for a trip across the sea aboard the royal ship The Dawn Treader. Along the way they encounter dragons, dwarves, merfolk, and a band of lost warriors before reaching the edge of the world.

title: Final Destination 3
text: In this third installment of the Final Destination series, a student's premonition of a deadly rollercoaster ride saves her life and a lucky few, but not from death itself which seeks out those who escaped their fate.

title: Trading Places
text: A snobbish investor and a wily street con artist find their positions reversed as part of a bet by two callous millionaires.

title: A Serious Man
text: Larry Gopnik, a Midwestern physics teacher, watches his life unravel over multiple sudden incidents. Though seeking meaning and answers amidst his turmoils, he seems to keep sinking.

title: The Rocky Horror Picture Show
text: A newly engaged couple have a breakdown in an isolated area and must pay a call to the bizarre residence of Dr. Frank-N-Furter.

title: We Were Soldiers
text: The story of the first major battle of the American phase of the Vietnam War and the soldiers on both sides that fought it.

title: Ransom
text: When a rich man's son is kidnapped, he cooperates with the police at first but then tries a unique tactic against the criminals.

title: Star Trek: First Contact
text: Captain Picard and his crew pursue the Borg back in time to stop them from preventing Earth's first contact with an alien species. They also make sure that Zefram Cochrane makes his famous maiden flight at warp speed.

title: From Paris with Love
text: In Paris, a young employee in the office of the US Ambassador hooks up with an American spy looking to stop a terrorist attack in the city.

title: Grown Ups 2
text: After moving his family back to his hometown to be with his friends and their kids, Lenny finds out that between old bullies, new bullies, schizo bus drivers, drunk cops on skis, and 400 costumed party crashers sometimes crazy follows you.

title: Raising Arizona
text: When a childless couple of an ex-con and an ex-cop decide to help themselves to one of another family's quintupelets, their lives get more complicated than they anticipated.

title: The Brothers Grimm
text: Will and Jake Grimm are traveling con-artists who encounter a genuine fairy-tale curse which requires true courage instead of their usual bogus exorcisms.

title: Robots
text: In a robot world, a young idealistic inventor travels to the big city to join his inspiration's company, only to find himself opposing its sinister new management.

title: Deep Blue Sea
text: Searching for a cure to Alzheimer's disease a group of scientists on an isolated research facility become the bait as a trio of intelligent sharks fight back.

title: My Big Fat Greek Wedding
text: A young Greek woman falls in love with a non-Greek and struggles to get her family to accept him while she comes to terms with her heritage and cultural identity.

title: Dune
text: A Duke's son leads desert warriors against the galactic emperor and his father's evil nemesis when they assassinate his father and free their desert world from the emperor's rule.

title: Highlander
text: An immortal Scottish swordsman must confront the last of his immortal opponent, a murderously brutal barbarian who lusts for the fabled "Prize".

title: Thelma & Louise
text: An Arkansas waitress and a housewife shoot a rapist and take off in a '66 Thunderbird.

title: Street Kings
text: An undercover cop, disillusioned by the recent murder of his wife, is implicated in the murder of an officer and must struggle to clear himself.

title: The Skin I Live In
text: A brilliant plastic surgeon, haunted by past tragedies, creates a type of synthetic skin that withstands any kind of damage. His guinea pig: a mysterious and volatile woman who holds the key to his obsession.

title: Billy Elliot
text: A talented young boy becomes torn between his unexpected love of dance and the disintegration of his family.

title: The Master
text: A Naval veteran arrives home from war unsettled and uncertain of his future - until he is tantalized by The Cause and its charismatic leader.

title: Kung Fu Hustle
text: In Shanghai, China in the 1940s, a wannabe gangster aspires to join the notorious "Axe Gang" while residents of a housing complex exhibit extraordinary powers in defending their turf.

title: Safety Not Guaranteed
text: Three magazine employees head out on an assignment to interview a guy who placed a classified ad seeking a companion for time travel.

title: Ghost World
text: With only the plan of moving in together after high school, two unusually devious friends seek direction in life. As a mere gag, they respond to a man's newspaper ad for a date, only to find it will greatly complicate their lives.

title: Priest
text: A priest disobeys church law to track down the vampires who kidnapped his niece.

title: The Scorpion King
text: A desert warrior rises up against the evil army that is destroying his homeland. He captures the enemy's key sorcerer, takes her deep into the desert and prepares for a final showdown.

title: Capote
text: In 1959, Truman Capote learns of the murder of a Kansas family and decides to write a book about the case. While researching for his novel In Cold Blood, Capote forms a relationship with one of the killers, Perry Smith, who is on death row.

title: Cinderella
text: When Cinderella's cruel stepmother prevents her from attending the Royal Ball, she gets some unexpected help from the lovable mice Gus and Jaq, and from her Fairy Godmother.

title: Magic Mike
text: A male stripper teaches a younger performer how to party, pick up women, and make easy money.

title: A Bronx Tale
text: A father becomes worried when a local gangster befriends his son in the Bronx in the 1960s.

title: Hairspray
text: Pleasantly plump teenager Tracy Turnblad teaches 1962 Baltimore a thing or two about integration after landing a spot on a local TV dance show.

title: Pay It Forward
text: A young boy attempts to make the world a better place after his teacher gives him that chance.

title: John Q
text: A down-on-his luck father, whose insurance won't cover his son's heart transplant, takes the hospital's emergency room hostage until the doctors agree to perform the operation.

title: Dial M for Murder
text: An ex-tennis pro carries out a plot to murder his wife. When things go wrong, he improvises a brilliant plan B.

title: Poltergeist
text: As a family moves into their new home, they notice strange events that mostly affect their young daughter.

title: Hercules
text: Having endured his legendary twelve labors, Hercules, the Greek demigod, has his life as a sword-for-hire tested when the King of Thrace and his daughter seek his aid in defeating a tyrannical warlord.

title: Predator 2
text: Amidst a territorial gang war, a sophisticated alien hunter stalks the citizens of Los Angeles and the only man between him and his prey is veteran L.A.P.D. officer, Lieutenant Mike Harrigan.

title: Hostage
text: A failed police negotiator turned small town cop, must save the lives of a family held hostage, which draws him into a much more dangerous situation.

title: My Best Friend's Wedding
text: When a woman's long-time friend says he's engaged, she realizes she loves him herself... and sets out to get him, with only days before the wedding.

title: Rat Race
text: A Las Vegas casino magnate, determined to find a new avenue for wagering, sets up a race for money.

title: One Day
text: After spending the night together on the night of their college graduation Dexter and Em are shown each year on the same date to see where they are in their lives. They are sometimes together, sometimes not, on that day.

title: Red Eye
text: A woman is kidnapped by a stranger on a routine flight. Threatened by the potential murder of her father, she is pulled into a plot to assist her captor in offing a politician.

title: Little Children
text: The lives of two lovelorn spouses from separate marriages, a registered sex offender, and a disgraced ex-police officer intersect as they struggle to resist their vulnerabilities and temptations in suburban Connecticut.

title: Akira
text: A secret military project endangers Neo-Tokyo when it turns a biker gang member into a rampaging psionic psychopath that only two kids and a group of psionics can stop.

title: The Phantom of the Opera
text: A young soprano becomes the obsession of a disfigured musical genius who lives beneath the Paris OpÃ©ra House.

title: Water for Elephants
text: A veterinary student abandons his studies after his parents are killed and joins a traveling circus as their vet.

title: Scream 3
text: While Sidney and her friends visit the Hollywood set of Stab 3, the third film based on the Woodsboro murders, a new Ghostface begins to terrorize them once again.

title: Lost Highway
text: After a bizarre encounter at a party, a jazz saxophonist is framed for the murder of his wife and sent to prison, where he inexplicably morphs into a young mechanic and begins leading a new life.

title: The Curse of the Were-Rabbit
text: Wallace and his loyal dog, Gromit, set out to discover the mystery behind the garden sabotage that plagues their village and threatens the annual giant vegetable growing contest.

title: A Time to Kill
text: A young lawyer defends a black man accused of murdering two men who raped his 10-year-old daughter, sparking a rebirth of the K.K.K.

title: La Haine
text: After local youth Abdel is beaten unconscious by police, a riot ensues on his estate during which a policeman loses his gun. The gun is found by Vinz who threatens he will kill a cop if Abdel dies.

title: TRON
text: A computer hacker is abducted into the digital world and forced to participate in gladiatorial games where his only chance of escape is with the help of a heroic security program.

title: The Invention of Lying
text: A comedy set in a world where no one has ever lied, until a writer seizes the opportunity for personal gain.

title: Premium Rush
text: In Manhattan, a bike messenger picks up an envelope that attracts the interest of a dirty cop, who pursues the cyclist throughout the city.

title: Miami Vice
text: Based on the 1980s TV action/drama, this update focuses on vice detectives Crockett and Tubbs as their respective personal and professional lives become dangerously intertwined.

title: White Chicks
text: Two disgraced FBI agents go way undercover in an effort to protect hotel heiresses the Wilson Sisters from a kidnapping plot.

title: City of Angels
text: Inspired by the modern classic, Wings of Desire, City involves an angel (Cage) who is spotted by a doctor in an operating room. Franz plays Cage's buddy who somehow knows a lot about angels.

title: Seven Years in Tibet
text: True story of Heinrich Harrer, an Austrian mountain climber who became friends with the Dalai Lama at the time of China's takeover of Tibet.

title: On the Waterfront
text: An ex-prize fighter turned longshoreman struggles to stand up to his corrupt union bosses.

title: Kramer vs. Kramer
text: A just-divorced man must learn to care for his son on his own, and then must fight in court to keep custody of him.

title: Leaving Las Vegas
text: Ben Sanderson, an alcoholic Hollywood screenwriter who lost everything because of his drinking, arrives in Las Vegas to drink himself to death. There, he meets and forms an uneasy friendship and non-interference pact with prostitute Sera.

title: Across the Universe
text: The music of the Beatles and the Vietnam War form the backdrop for the romance between an upper-class American girl and a poor Liverpudlian artist.

title: Cliffhanger
text: A botched mid-air heist results in suitcases full of cash being searched for by various groups throughout the Rocky Mountains.

title: Valentine's Day
text: Intertwining couples and singles in Los Angeles break-up and make-up based on the pressures and expectations of Valentine's Day.

title: Shanghai Noon
text: A Chinese man who travels to the Wild West to rescue a kidnapped princess. After teaming up with a train robber, the unlikely duo takes on a Chinese traitor and his corrupt boss.

title: Good Morning, Vietnam
text: An unorthodox and irreverent DJ begins to shake up things when he is assigned to the US Armed Services Radio station in Vietnam.

title: Tombstone
text: A successful lawman's plans to retire anonymously in Tombstone, Arizona, are disrupted by the kind of outlaws he was famous for eliminating.

title: House of Wax
text: A group of unwitting teens are stranded near a strange wax museum and soon must fight to survive and keep from becoming the next exhibit.

title: The Addams Family
text: Con artists plan to fleece the eccentric family using an accomplice who claims to be their long lost Uncle Fester.

title: M
text: When the police in a German city are unable to catch a child-murderer, other criminals join in the manhunt.

title: The Monuments Men
text: An unlikely World War II platoon is tasked to rescue art masterpieces from Nazi thieves and return them to their owners.

title: Freaky Friday
text: An overworked mother and her daughter do not get along. When they switch bodies, each is forced to adapt to the others life for one freaky Friday.

title: The Bounty Hunter
text: A bounty hunter learns that his next target is his ex-wife, a reporter working on a murder cover-up. Soon after their reunion, the always-at-odds duo find themselves on a run-for-their-lives adventure.

title: Outbreak
text: Extreme measures are necessary to contain an epidemic of a deadly airborne virus. But how extreme, exactly?

title: The Jacket
text: A Gulf war veteran is wrongly sent to a mental institution for insane criminals, where he becomes the object of a Doctor's experiments, and his life is completely affected by them.

title: Scary Movie 4
text: Cindy finds out the house she lives in is haunted by a little boy and goes on a quest to find out who killed him and why. Also, Alien "Tr-iPods" are invading the world and she has to uncover the secret in order to stop them.

title: Tears of the Sun
text: A Special-Ops commander leads his team into the Nigerian jungle in order to rescue a doctor who will only join them if they agree to save 70 refugees too.

title: The Thing
text: At an Antarctica research site, the discovery of an alien craft leads to a confrontation between graduate student Kate Lloyd and scientist Dr. Sander Halvorson.

title: Babe
text: Babe, a pig raised by sheepdogs, learns to herd sheep with a little help from Farmer Hoggett.

title: The Faculty
text: Students suspect that their teachers are aliens after bizarre occurances.

title: Blazing Saddles
text: To ruin a western town, a corrupt political boss appoints a black sheriff, who promptly becomes his most formidable adversary.

title: Cars 2
text: Star race car Lightning McQueen and his pal Mater head overseas to compete in the World Grand Prix race. But the road to the championship becomes rocky as Mater gets caught up in an intriguing adventure of his own: international espionage.

title: The Crazies
text: About the inhabitants of a small Iowa town suddenly plagued by insanity and then death after a mysterious toxin contaminates their water supply.

title: The Exorcism of Emily Rose
text: A lawyer takes on a negligent homicide case involving a priest who performed an exorcism on a young girl.

title: House of Flying Daggers
text: A romantic police captain breaks a beautiful member of a rebel group out of prison to help her rejoin her fellows, but things are not what they seem.

title: The Wolfman
text: Upon his return to his ancestral homeland, an American man is bitten, and subsequently cursed by, a werewolf.

title: The Diving Bell and the Butterfly
text: The true story of Elle editor Jean-Dominique Bauby who suffers a stroke and has to live with an almost totally paralyzed body; only his left eye isn't paralyzed.

title: Running Scared
text: A low-ranking thug is entrusted by his crime boss to dispose of a gun that killed corrupt cops, but things get out of control when the gun ends up in wrong hands.

title: Jennifer's Body
text: A newly possessed high school cheerleader turns into a succubus who specializes in killing her male classmates. Can her best friend put an end to the horror?

title: Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit
text: Jack Ryan, as a young covert CIA analyst, uncovers a Russian plot to crash the U.S. economy with a terrorist attack.

title: Wild Things
text: A police detective uncovers a conspiracy behind a case involving a high-school guidance counselor when accusations of rape are made against him by two female students.

title: Paycheck
text: What seemed like a breezy idea for an engineer to net him millions of dollars, leaves him on the run for his life and piecing together why he's being chased.

title: The Whole Nine Yards
text: Nick is a struggling dentist in Canada. A new neighbor moves in, and he discovers that it is Jimmy "The Tulip" Teduski. His wife convinces him to go to Chicago and inform the mob boss who wants Jimmy dead.

title: Aliens vs. Predator: Requiem
text: Warring alien and predator races descend on a small town, where unsuspecting residents must band together for any chance of survival.

title: Y Tu Mamá También
text: In Mexico, two teenage boys and an attractive older woman embark on a road trip and learn a thing or two about life, friendship, sex, and each other.

title: The Texas Chain Saw Massacre
text: Five friends visiting their grandfather's house in the country are hunted and terrorized by a chain-saw wielding killer and his family of grave-robbing cannibals.

title: Pirate Radio
text: A period comedy about an illegal radio station in the North Sea in the 1960s.

title: The Hunchback of Notre Dame
text: A deformed bell-ringer must assert his independence from a vicious government minister in order to help his friend, a gypsy dancer.

title: Papillon
text: A man befriends a fellow criminal as the two of them begin serving their sentence on a dreadful prison island, which inspires the man to plot his escape.

title: Something's Gotta Give
text: A swinger on the cusp of being a senior citizen with a taste for young women falls in love with an accomplished woman closer to his age.

title: Push
text: Two young Americans with special abilities must race to find a girl in Hong Kong before a shadowy government organization called Division does.

title: Frost/Nixon
text: A dramatic retelling of the post-Watergate television interviews between British talk-show host David Frost and former president Richard Nixon.

title: Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan
text: With the assistance of the Enterprise crew, Admiral Kirk must stop an old nemesis, Khan Noonien Singh, from using his son's life-generating device, the Genesis Device, as the ultimate weapon.

title: Epic Movie
text: A comedic satire of films that are large in scope, reputation and popularity

title: The Other Woman
text: After discovering her boyfriend is married, Carly soon meets the wife he's been betraying. And when yet another love affair is discovered, all three women team up to plot revenge on the three-timing S.O.B.

title: Coyote Ugly
text: Aspiring songwriter Violet Sanford, after getting a job at a women-run NYC bar that teases its male patrons, comes out of her shell.

title: Identity Thief
text: Mild mannered businessman Sandy Patterson travels from Denver to Florida to confront the deceptively harmless looking woman who has been living it up after stealing Sandy's identity.

title: The Good Shepherd
text: The tumultuous early history of the Central Intelligence Agency is viewed through the prism of one man's life.

title: The Strangers
text: A young couple staying in an isolated vacation home are terrorized by three unknown assailants.

title: Animal House
text: At a 1962 College, Dean Vernon Wormer is determined to expel the entire Delta Tau Chi Fraternity, but those trouble-makers have other plans for him.

title: Meet the Spartans
text: The heroic Spartan king Leonidas, armed with nothing but leather underwear and a cape, leads a ragtag...

title: The Lost Boys
text: After moving to a new town, two brothers are convinced that the area is frequented by vampires.

title: Charlie Wilson's War
text: A drama based on a Texas congressman Charlie Wilson's covert dealings in Afghanistan, where his efforts to assist rebels in their war with the Soviets have some unforeseen and long-reaching effects.

title: Sleeping Beauty
text: After being snubbed by the royal family, a malevolent fairy places a curse on a princess which only a prince can break, along with the help of three good fairies.

title: Death at a Funeral
text: Chaos ensues when a man tries to expose a dark secret regarding a recently deceased patriarch of a dysfunctional British family.

title: Gothika
text: A repressed female psychiatrist wakes up as a patient in the asylum where she worked, with no memory of why she is there or what she has done.

title: Let Me In
text: A bullied young boy befriends a young female vampire who lives in secrecy with her guardian.

title: Dear John
text: A romantic drama about a soldier who falls for a conservative college student while he's home on leave.

title: Alpha Dog
text: A drama based on the life of Jesse James Hollywood, a drug dealer who became one of the youngest men ever to be on the FBI's most wanted list.

title: A Scanner Darkly
text: An undercover cop in a not-too-distant future becomes involved with a dangerous new drug and begins to lose his own identity as a result.

title: The Interpreter
text: Political intrigue and deception unfold inside the United Nations, where a U.S. Secret Service agent is assigned to investigate an interpreter who overhears an assassination plot.

title: Men of Honor
text: The story of Carl Brashear, the first African American, then also the first amputee, US Navy Diver and the man who trained him.

title: Repo Men
text: Set in the near future when artificial organs can be bought on credit, it revolves around a man who struggles to make the payments on a heart he has purchased. He must therefore go on the run before said ticker is repossessed.

title: Van Wilder
text: The most popular kid on campus meets a beautiful journalist who makes him realize that maybe he's afraid to graduate.

title: Bend It Like Beckham
text: The daughter of orthodox Sikh rebels against her parents' traditionalism by running off to Germany with a football team (soccer in America).

title: Boyz n the Hood
text: Saga of a group of childhood friends growing up in a Los Angeles ghetto.

title: Awakenings
text: The victims of an encephalitis epidemic many years ago have been catatonic ever since, but now a new drug offers the prospect of reviving them.

title: The Forbidden Kingdom
text: A discovery made by a kung fu obsessed American teen sends him on an adventure to China, where he joins up with a band of martial arts warriors in order to free the imprisoned Monkey King.

title: Dan in Real Life
text: A widower finds out the woman he fell in love with is his brother's girlfriend.
